17
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:45,000
[Episode 40]

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,990
I also hope

19
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:53,970
you can spend more time with me.

20
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:11,780
Let's get along like this in the days to come.

21
00:02:11,780 --> 00:02:13,670
Would it be nice?

22
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:25,230
You are a big girl. Don't cry.

23
00:02:32,930 --> 00:02:35,700
The practice we did just now is called communication practice.

24
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:38,560
In fact, in your daily conflict, the most destructive thing

25
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:42,840
is not the problem itself, but the destructive way in which you are trying to communicate.

26
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:48,060
Back and forth with your blames, you've long forgotten what the problem is.

27
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:51,770
This is what you need to pay attention to in your daily life afterwards.

28
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:01,100
I just can't stop once I start talking.

29
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:07,133
Old Song, I'm sorry for a lot of things I did in the past.

30
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:13,600
In this stage of your marriage, the fear of losing each other paralyzes the relationship between you.

31
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:20,740
Actually, a rational, healthy family relation entails an independent space for each of you.

32
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:23,870
But I always can't control myself.

33
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,590
I keep thinking nonsense.

34
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:32,880
Now recall the time when you first started dating, did you also have the feelings of fear and anxiety?

35
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,420
I was young at that time.

36
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:37,260
I was also quite a looker.

37
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:40,740
I had a good job and got on with people well.

38
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:42,930
Back then, he was only too happy to take me as the apple of his eye.

39
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:45,680
So what was there to panic about?

40
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:51,290
Believe in the possibility of being independent from your partner

41
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:53,910
so that you'll have a clearer idea of the goal of your growth.

42
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:57,470
I believe you've already had an answer in your mind now.

43
00:03:58,370 --> 00:04:00,210
Miss He,

44
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:03,010
I've figured it out.

45
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:05,783
You are right.

46
00:04:05,783 --> 00:04:07,390
I can't always be dependent on him.

47
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,670
I must have my own life.

48
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,800
No, no. I don't want a divorce.

49
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:19,130
Did I say I'm going to divorce you?

50
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:52,130
Sister Tang. Sister Tang.

51
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:54,830
All right, Sister Tang. Don't pretend to be asleep.

52
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:57,120
We are not going to the counseling room today.

53
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:02,730
- Really?
- Yes.

54
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:06,720
Our hospital has introduced a batch of new apparatus for treating mental symptoms.

55
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:09,583
It has a similar effect to Valium.

56
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:13,050
I thought you hate going to the counseling room most, so I moved it here for you first.

57
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:16,890
This apparatus cost our hospital a hefty sum.

58
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,100
Then…

59
00:05:19,883 --> 00:05:23,170
Then I don't have to go to the counseling room from now on?

60
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:25,171
Right. You can be treated in the room.

61
00:05:25,171 --> 00:05:27,710
But you still have to take the medicine.

62
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:34,883
Here, Sister Tang.

63
00:05:51,930 --> 00:05:54,590
Let's try the apparatus.

64
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:07,560
Sister Tang, if we use this, we don't have to go to the counseling room later on.

65
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,273
Here.

66
00:06:09,273 --> 00:06:11,063
Try it.

67
00:06:21,910 --> 00:06:23,360
[Start]

68
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,340
This is the switch.

69
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:28,580
And you can press a few times to adjust the duration.

70
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:31,270
The one below is for the modes of massage.

71
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:35,053
You can adjust it to whatever massage mode you want.

72
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,250
Let me know anytime if it makes you feel uncomfortable.

73
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:56,910
Let go of me. I'm not doing it.

74
00:06:56,910 --> 00:06:58,930
I'm not doing it.

75
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:00,230
Take it easy. You'll be fine.

76
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,340
Let go of me. I'm not doing it.

77
00:07:01,340 --> 00:07:04,800
Put up with it, or I'll have to give you an injection and it'll give you pain.

78
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,510
I'm not doing it.

79
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:09,503
You are here.

80
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:14,070
Tell them I'm not doing this, OK?

81
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:15,630
Please.

82
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,213
Rest easy.

83
00:07:17,213 --> 00:07:21,180
This is the best private hospital I can find for you.

84
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:23,250
I don't want to do it.

85
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:27,120
I don't want to do it.

86
00:07:38,330 --> 00:07:39,963
Be good.

87
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:46,620
After this treatment, those unhappy things will slip your mind.

88
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,333
All right?

89
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:57,470
I'm not doing it! Let go of me! I'm not doing it…

90
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:58,960
You'll get better after this, all right?

91
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,600
I don't want it.

92
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,660
Jicheng, let go of your hold.

93
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:05,470
Can you let go of your hold?

94
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:07,000
- Go ahead.
- Let go of me.

95
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,330
Don't go.

96
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:12,400
Ye Jicheng, you are abusing your power.

97
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:16,310
The hospital said I don't need such treatment.

98
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,270
Please.

99
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:14,790
I'm not doing it!

100
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:16,230
What's wrong, Fu Tang?

101
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:18,180
Calm down, calm down. Calm down, calm down.

102
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:19,500
I'm not doing it.

103
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:24,540
Please give me a break. Please give me a break.

104
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,920
Please give me…

105
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,170
Are you feeling any better?

106
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,933
It's all right.

107
00:10:46,130 --> 00:10:48,063
I'm sorry.

108
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:53,580
I'm late.

109
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:01,540
I'll get you out of here now.

110
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,670
We've given the patient a shot of tranquilizer.

111
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:14,310
She'll be sleeping for a while.

112
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:15,840
How is the patient doing now?

113
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,250
According to the nurse who gave her the treatment today,

114
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:22,990
about five minutes into using the therapeutic apparatus, the patient began to have a stress reaction,

115
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:26,290
showing symptoms of convulsion and difficult breathing.

116
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:31,980
The nurse was in a panic back then, since the therapeutic apparatus has the effect of soothing emotions.

117
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:34,130
Such a problem shouldn't have occurred.

118
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:38,240
Before using this therapeutic apparatus, have you done a health assessment on Auntie Fu?

119
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,640
Yes, you reminded us repeatedly before.

120
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,440
We must take it seriously.

121
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:46,610
What's more, the patient was in a very stable condition overall.

122
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:48,910
We don't know why this happened.

123
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:52,750
Is Auntie Fu the only one who's had this symptom?

124
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:55,811
To be frank, after this incident happened today, I learned that

125
00:11:55,811 --> 00:11:59,480
similar incidents actually happened a few days ago.

126
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:02,970
Just that the symptoms of headache and dizziness that other patients had

127
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:06,720
are their normal conditions, so we didn't pay much attention.

128
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:09,720
This was indeed negligence of duty on our part.

129
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:12,720
I hereby apologize to you on behalf of our staff.

130
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:16,650
No, no. I understand. It was not entirely your fault.

131
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:20,983
That's to say that whatsit therapeutic apparatus is out of order?

132
00:12:20,983 --> 00:12:22,430
That's very likely.

133
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:27,080
We've already sent a complaint report to the apparatus provider and asked them to give us an explanation.

134
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:32,050
Before we find out the truth of this incident, we will not use the apparatus on other patients again.

135
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:33,550
What venal businessmen they are!

136
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,180
They've even messed with medical devices.

137
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:38,160
Could you show us the apparatus?

138
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,110
I'll go with you.

139
00:12:49,990 --> 00:12:52,340
Here it is. Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation Device.

140
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:53,740
Also known as aRMS.

141
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:56,170
This is the manual.

142
00:12:56,170 --> 00:12:59,310
Could such a tiny contraption do so much harm?

143
00:12:59,310 --> 00:13:00,720
Is this a new device?

144
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,110
Yes, it's new.

145
00:13:02,110 --> 00:13:04,230
We used another provider's before.

146
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:07,020
Some time ago, our sanatorium needed to purchase a batch of new devices.

147
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:12,770
They happened to be doing promotions and their devices have complete functions, so we ordered a batch of them.

148
00:13:12,770 --> 00:13:16,290
Are such therapeutic apparatus used only in sanatoriums?

149
00:13:16,910 --> 00:13:21,250
If approved, they could also be promoted in specialized and general hospitals.

150
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:22,900
Are you sure?

151
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:27,940
In principle, therapeutic apparatus of such specifications have a very high level of safety

152
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:30,230
with endorsement of the Psychological Society.

153
00:13:30,230 --> 00:13:33,260
How could such a thing happen?

154
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:35,893
- Unless…
- Unless what?

155
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:38,010
That's not possible.

156
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:41,980
The Society couldn't have possibly approved such a substandard product.

157
00:13:41,980 --> 00:13:44,340
This won't do. I must turn to someone for verification.

158
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:45,710
- Thanks.
- No problem.

159
00:13:45,710 --> 00:13:47,350
Professor Ji is no longer with the Society.

160
00:13:47,350 --> 00:13:49,210
Who are you going to turn to for verification?

161
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:54,371
Approval of such psychotherapy devices is supposed to be done by the EEG Technology Committee.

162
00:13:54,371 --> 00:13:55,910
I know who to turn to.

163
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:58,243
- Who?
- Who?

164
00:13:58,243 --> 00:13:59,890
You know this person as well.

165
00:13:59,890 --> 00:14:03,200
The new president Wen Liang.

166
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,980
What are you doing?

167
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,510
Get out of here. Mom.

168
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:20,820
Lili. Lili.

169
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:22,520
What are you doing in broad daylight?

170
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,020
Your daughter is here.

171
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:27,611
You are dressed to kill. You don't look like you are short of cash.

172
00:14:27,611 --> 00:14:29,840
It seems you can pay the money back anyway today, right?

173
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,320
You choose to be a thug instead of a good man.

174
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:32,640
Does your mother know about this?

175
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,910
Who are you cursing?

176
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:35,860
Are you justified in owing money?

177
00:14:35,860 --> 00:14:37,250
I tell you what, don't touch me!

178
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:38,620
I'm going to call the police. Don't you believe me?

179
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:40,653
Go ahead.

180
00:14:40,653 --> 00:14:43,040
This girl is so pretty when she gets angry.

181
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:43,980
My cup of tea.

182
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:46,620
It is me who owes you money. It has nothing to do with my daughter.

183
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:47,910
You guys mustn't touch my daughter!

184
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:49,690
What are you talking about?

185
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:51,800
Can you pay it back?

186
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,810
Why didn't I see you show such spunk just now?

187
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,343
Why?

188
00:14:56,343 --> 00:14:57,990
Are you emboldened by your daughter's presence?

189
00:14:57,990 --> 00:15:00,410
I tell you what, she's your senior after all.

190
00:15:00,410 --> 00:15:03,160
Haven't your mother taught you to respect the old and care for the young?

191
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:05,640
I'm going to call the police if you come any closer. Don't you believe me?

192
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,073
Go ahead.

193
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:10,100
Feel free to do so. Are you stupid or something?

194
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:13,000
Your mother is the debtor who owes me money and I'm the creditor who comes to collect my debt.

195
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,890
If you have no money, you should kneel down to beg me.

196
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:19,110
Shouldn't this be the attitude of paying back a debt?

197
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:22,330
For the sake of your pretty face, I can give you a grace period of a few days.

198
00:15:22,330 --> 00:15:24,080
Don't be so unappreciative.

199
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,700
Even ready to call the police?

200
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:30,690
I tell you what, it's not good for anyone if you piss us off.

201
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:32,670
Figure it out yourself.

202
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:37,443
Mom, how much did you borrow?

203
00:15:37,443 --> 00:15:39,760
I… I didn't borrow much.

204
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,840
My store keeps losing money, so I just borrowed no more than a hundred thousand yuan

205
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:45,350
as working capital and I'll pay it back later.

206
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:47,860
Who knows… You were playing mahjong again, weren't you?

207
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:49,540
I…I…

208
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:52,150
You've started talking?

209
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:54,910
I see you and your daughter are having a hard time.

210
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,243
Here.

211
00:15:57,650 --> 00:16:02,450
Put your thumb print on here and I'll give you a grace period.

212
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:06,800
Don't dilly-dally.

213
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,650
The interest rate is higher, but you are given more time.

214
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:11,740
You can save your life first and make money later.

215
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:15,200
I'm helping you because of your pretty face.

216
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:17,670
Don't touch me! Go away!

217
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:21,750
Let me teach you a lesson today.

218
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,183
Stop!

219
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,210
I squeeze…

220
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:37,610
What the hell! What the hell!

221
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:47,990
Let's go. He's a cop.

222
00:16:50,550 --> 00:16:52,183
Piss off!

223
00:16:56,210 --> 00:16:59,511
Well, I… I'll go and call the police.

224
00:16:59,511 --> 00:17:01,083
Are you all right?

225
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:05,900
What happened to you?

226
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:09,660
I…I'm all right. A minor injury.

227
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:12,733
Thank you.

228
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:14,373
You can go.

229
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:18,261
I'm not going. They've just left. I'm worried.

230
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,660
Just cry if you want to.

231
00:17:27,660 --> 00:17:29,620
I'm here with you.

232
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:31,150
Go. I don't want to see you.

233
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,791
I just got here. Why do you ask me to go?

234
00:17:32,791 --> 00:17:34,550
I don't want you to see me end up like this.

235
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:36,330
You look good like this. I don't mind.

236
00:17:36,330 --> 00:17:38,460
I do!

237
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:53,083
Lili, I've done some serious soul-searching.

238
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:56,260
I will always stay by your side to protect you.

239
00:17:56,260 --> 00:17:58,260
You can't drive me away.

240
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,520
You are the one I'm sure to marry.

241
00:18:16,150 --> 00:18:18,600
Did I say I'm going to marry you?

242
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,860
Miss Wen, please have a cup of coffee.

243
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:35,320
Thanks.

244
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:38,810
It must be very interesting experience working in such an environment.

245
00:18:38,810 --> 00:18:41,231
Not bad. At first, I felt a bit like a fish out of water.

246
00:18:41,231 --> 00:18:43,490
But I'm doing much better now.

247
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:45,210
I've listened to your show.

248
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:51,000
The episode on ethical relations of psychological counselors struck home with me.

249
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,970
Thank you for liking my show.

250
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:58,640
Miss Wen, I asked you over this time since I have a very serious question to ask you.

251
00:18:59,210 --> 00:19:01,040
If there is something wrong with the aRMS therapeutic apparatus

252
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:04,420
approved by the Ethics Accreditation of the Psychological Society,

253
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:08,200
can we ask the Psychological Society to publicize the security data of the apparatus?

254
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,310
- Is there something wrong?
- Yes.

255
00:19:10,310 --> 00:19:15,340
One of my patients showed strong stress reaction after using it.

256
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:19,160
And as far as I know, this has happened to more than one patient.

257
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:22,880
The clinical trials of the aRMS therapeutic apparatus showed nothing wrong.

258
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:27,160
I can see the occurrence of such incidents makes you skeptical of the safety of the apparatus.

259
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:30,700
But there are many possibilities that could lead to a patient's stress reaction.

260
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,561
And as to whether a patient's health status meets the conditions

261
00:19:32,561 --> 00:19:36,580
for using the apparatus, I think this should be the...

262
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,840
focus of your investigation.

263
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:45,900
Miss Wen, I've double-checked this scenario.

264
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:49,750
I've basically ruled out the patient's own health problem.

265
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:53,390
Besides, such kind of therapeutic apparatus currently available on the market is very safe.

266
00:19:53,390 --> 00:19:56,470
Such stress reaction is not commonplace.

267
00:19:56,470 --> 00:20:00,960
And I've found quite a few cases like this in such a small scope,

268
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:03,780
so this is not an emergency.

269
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:07,510
Have you found out more about the specific circumstances of other patients in the sanatorium?

270
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:12,070
What I know is after their first usage, they didn't feel very pleasant,

271
00:20:12,070 --> 00:20:14,500
so they refused to use it for a second time.

272
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,780
All right then.

273
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:19,171
I'll go back and check if there are any problems with the technical indicators.

274
00:20:19,171 --> 00:20:20,920
But the possibility is low.

275
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:24,690
Once there is a problem, I'll certainly take up the matter myself.

276
00:20:24,690 --> 00:20:27,700
Thank you, Miss Wen. I hope it won't give you trouble.

277
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:30,410
Thank you for coming to me first.

278
00:20:30,410 --> 00:20:31,590
I'm off for now.

279
00:20:31,590 --> 00:20:34,180
- Thank you.
- Thank you for your coffee.

280
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,850
How was the conversation?

281
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:55,180
Did you say the aRMS therapeutic apparatus is only used in sanatoriums?

282
00:20:55,180 --> 00:20:56,170
No.

283
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:59,530
Specialized hospitals and relevant treatment facilities are promoting and using it as well.

284
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:01,410
Ye Jiahui said it.

285
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,780
But it's so weird.

286
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:08,990
Why did she take it for granted that my patient is from a sanatorium?

287
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,930
Lili, slow down.

288
00:21:13,930 --> 00:21:16,781
If you make me injured again, I'm going to extort money from you.

289
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:24,370
Let go of me. Let go of me.

290
00:21:24,370 --> 00:21:26,330
Let me have a word with you.

291
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,780
Why did you disappear into thin air?

292
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:35,680
Where have you been?

293
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,200
Why did you get injured like this?

294
00:21:42,190 --> 00:21:44,040
I was on a mission.

295
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,873
What mission?

296
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:49,700
My work unit asks us to keep it secret.

297
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:52,910
Can't you say a few more words?

298
00:21:52,910 --> 00:21:55,253
Yes.

299
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,470
I missed you so much.

300
00:22:05,230 --> 00:22:07,150
Did you miss me?

301
00:22:08,740 --> 00:22:10,260
I don't know.

302
00:22:10,260 --> 00:22:12,570
How could you not know?

303
00:22:16,950 --> 00:22:19,660
Are you a fool?

304
00:22:19,660 --> 00:22:23,380
I also think I've become a fool since I started dating you.

305
00:22:40,370 --> 00:22:42,303
Does it hurt?

306
00:22:43,160 --> 00:22:44,793
Lili,

307
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,373
I'm sorry.

308
00:22:50,430 --> 00:22:53,920
So you missed me as well, right?

309
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:57,020
Can you stop asking me such a silly question?

310
00:22:59,210 --> 00:23:01,500
How did you find my mother's store?

311
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,490
Don't you have the slightest clue? You've been to the police station so many times.

312
00:23:04,490 --> 00:23:07,780
You are already our key object of protection.

313
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:20,750
[Flower Coffee House]

314
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,000
What goodies are these?

315
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,240
Mageline. Qing Qing gave them to me.

316
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,810
She says they are good for my scalp.

317
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:32,210
Ask her to give some of these goodies to me too.

318
00:23:32,210 --> 00:23:34,360
No.

319
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:37,830
Qing Qing specially gave them to me.

320
00:23:37,830 --> 00:23:39,190
Do you want some too?

321
00:23:39,190 --> 00:23:41,560
- This month's hot review.
- I'm on it.

322
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:42,990
- Topic selection.
- I'll do it.

323
00:23:42,990 --> 00:23:44,820
- Hotline.
- I'm on it.

324
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:48,380
Work a graveyard shift for me tonight.

325
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:49,713
OK.

326
00:23:49,713 --> 00:23:51,373
Keep them safe.

327
00:23:52,740 --> 00:23:54,810
Let's get a move on. In case we disturb Boss.

328
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:56,533
Yes.

329
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:09,210
I can see the occurrence of such incidents

330
00:24:09,210 --> 00:24:11,160
makes you skeptical of the safety of the apparatus.

331
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:14,770
But there are many possibilities that could lead to a patient's stress reaction.

332
00:24:14,770 --> 00:24:16,561
And as to whether a patient's health status meets the conditions

333
00:24:16,561 --> 00:24:20,680
for using the apparatus, I think this should be the...

334
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:27,280
focus of your investigation.

335
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:30,010
You've been absent-minded for quite a while.

336
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:32,110
What are you thinking?

337
00:24:32,110 --> 00:24:33,790
Something is not right.

338
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:35,560
What is not right?

339
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:39,160
Are you talking about Wen Liang?

340
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:49,831
Thank you both. I'll support you guys forever.

341
00:24:56,620 --> 00:25:00,030
Mr. Qian, you… you are too close to me.

342
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:02,180
I refuse to be tied with you. Don't ride on my coattails for popularity.

343
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:04,780
Miss He, my relationship with you is open and aboveboard.

344
00:25:04,780 --> 00:25:06,880
I'm not afraid of gossips.

345
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:10,400
I'll stop teasing you.

346
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,560
So do you mean Wen Liang blurted out

347
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:16,340
and asked you whether other patients in the sanatorium had any reactions?

348
00:25:16,340 --> 00:25:21,340
When she said the word sanatorium, she said it unambiguously and she was even quite convinced.

349
00:25:21,340 --> 00:25:25,431
So you suspect she knew what you were doing in the sanatorium?

350
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:28,210
It is fair to say so.

351
00:25:30,980 --> 00:25:33,520
If now you are asked to say a name of a café…

352
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,630
Flower Garden. What's wrong?

353
00:25:35,630 --> 00:25:36,960
Don't you think so?

354
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:40,130
It's easier for us to blurt out names of places that we often hear, see and go to.

355
00:25:40,130 --> 00:25:41,830
She must go to the sanatorium often.

356
00:25:41,830 --> 00:25:45,370
That's why she knew your patient is in the sanatorium.

357
00:25:45,370 --> 00:25:47,940
The "you guys" as she mentioned refers to us.

358
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:49,690
What you guys and us?

359
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:50,860
What do you mean?

360
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:55,040
When she was saying "you guys", she shifted her eyes to another direction.

361
00:25:57,290 --> 00:25:58,840
She was looking at you.

362
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:02,360
So she thought we were caring for a patient in the sanatorium.

363
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:03,500
So what?

364
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:07,230
Unless she has really seen us in the sanatorium.

365
00:26:08,620 --> 00:26:12,110
Otherwise according to her logical analysis, a psychological counselor

366
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:15,850
could not possibly take her friend with her to engage with a patient.

367
00:26:26,030 --> 00:26:27,463
Mr. Ye.

368
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:34,120
These are a dozen complaint reports we've received.

369
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:37,020
The feedback for this batch of apparatus is not very good.

370
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:53,260
A machine is a machine after all.

371
00:26:53,260 --> 00:26:55,920
Machines will have to break down.

372
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,290
Send people of the technical department to have a look.

373
00:26:58,290 --> 00:27:01,110
Recall a product where a recall is due. Give compensation where a compensation is due.

374
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:03,180
They've been there. The other side does not accept a compensation.

375
00:27:03,180 --> 00:27:05,891
That's because your compensation is not big enough!

376
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:10,003
Get out.

377
00:27:18,430 --> 00:27:20,263
Miss Wen?

378
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:23,760
I heard some bad news these past few days.

379
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:26,060
I hastened to come and talk about it with you.

380
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:32,530
These days, quite a few patients have started using the apparatus.

381
00:27:32,530 --> 00:27:36,300
They showed symptoms of stress later on and some of the patients began to resist using it.

382
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:40,170
I wonder if the first batch of apparatus has any safety problems.

383
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:43,040
You are not talking about safety problems.

384
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:45,290
You are talking about customer feedback.

385
00:27:45,290 --> 00:27:47,850
Since it is feedback, it's bound to be a mixture of good and bad.

386
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:52,140
Besides, our customers… are somewhat special.

387
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:53,330
What do you say?

388
00:27:53,330 --> 00:27:56,530
We should lose no time to recall and test the first batch of apparatus

389
00:27:56,530 --> 00:27:59,430
and do a systematic safety assessment.

390
00:28:00,110 --> 00:28:05,480
You are an expert in psychological counseling and I'm an expert in technological invention.

391
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:07,500
As to whether the apparatus is good or not,

392
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:10,820
it is not up to you to have the final say, nor the customers.

393
00:28:10,820 --> 00:28:12,100
It is up to the quality inspection report.

394
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:13,660
Something has gone wrong already so far.

395
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:15,810
I signed my name on the approval document.

396
00:28:15,810 --> 00:28:18,260
I take full responsibility.

397
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:26,450
Otherwise, why do you think

398
00:28:28,020 --> 00:28:31,400
I put you in that position?

399
00:28:36,780 --> 00:28:39,790
Are you not afraid you'll shoot yourself in the foot?

400
00:28:39,790 --> 00:28:42,880
In the sanatorium He Dun visits, there has already been something wrong with the apparatus.

401
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:45,810
Ji Mingcong certainly will not sit back.

402
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,650
You've found Fu Tang?

403
00:29:10,330 --> 00:29:13,310
I'd like to sit on the balcony.

404
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:17,100
All right. I'll take you there after I take your blood pressure, okay?

405
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:19,100
Relax.

406
00:29:24,660 --> 00:29:27,180
Excuse me, could you tell me which floor the Inpatient Department is on?

407
00:29:27,180 --> 00:29:28,450
It's on the 13th floor.

408
00:29:28,450 --> 00:29:30,083
Thanks a lot.

409
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:03,220
[Visitor Information Center]

410
00:30:11,410 --> 00:30:13,143
Hello.

411
00:30:13,143 --> 00:30:14,650
Hello, Sir.

412
00:30:14,650 --> 00:30:17,060
Could you please tell me which room is Ms. Fu Tang staying in?

413
00:30:17,060 --> 00:30:18,210
Could you please let me know who you are?

414
00:30:18,210 --> 00:30:19,920
I'm her family member.

415
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:22,050
Sir, the visiting hours have passed.

416
00:30:22,050 --> 00:30:24,350
Please come earlier next time.

417
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:27,260
I'm busy most of the time. Could you make an exception?

418
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:29,070
Sir, the visiting hours have passed.

419
00:30:29,070 --> 00:30:31,720
Please come earlier next time.

420
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:34,520
It's like this. She's my wife.

421
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:36,810
- You see…
- Sir, the visiting hours have passed.

422
00:30:36,810 --> 00:30:39,010
Please come earlier next time.

423
00:30:46,060 --> 00:30:47,870
Sir, it's the end of our working hours.

424
00:30:47,870 --> 00:30:51,011
Please contact the patient you'd like to visit yourself.

425
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:16,350
It's a nice day today.

426
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:18,350
Would you like to go out for a walk?

427
00:31:54,140 --> 00:31:55,510
Mom, where are you going?

428
00:31:55,510 --> 00:31:58,700
Did you have a row with dad again?

429
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:01,450
Get out of the way.

430
00:32:02,430 --> 00:32:04,090
Go away!

431
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:06,580
Go away. Don't hold me. Go away.

432
00:32:06,580 --> 00:32:09,210
Get out of the way!

433
00:32:22,900 --> 00:32:24,380
Where are you going?

434
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:25,900
It's raining outside.

435
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:27,410
You haven't had dinner yet.

436
00:32:27,410 --> 00:32:28,860
How does this sound?

437
00:32:28,860 --> 00:32:33,910
When the weather clears up tomorrow, our son and I will hang out with you, all right?

438
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,310
- All right?
- Okay.

439
00:32:35,310 --> 00:32:37,040
- Where are we going?
- To the zoo.

440
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:39,540
- To the zoo? What are you gonna look at in the zoo?
- Monkeys.

441
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:41,351
Look at monkeys? Are you a little monkey?

442
00:32:41,351 --> 00:32:43,741
I'm a monkey. I'm a little monkey. I'm gonna climb a tree.

443
00:32:43,741 --> 00:32:45,850
You are going to climb a tree?

444
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:50,960
Do you love him a lot?

445
00:32:54,930 --> 00:32:56,763
I love you too.

446
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:12,100
But it's such a pity

447
00:33:14,780 --> 00:33:17,920
that he is Ji Mingcong's child.

448
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:34,310
I was telling the truth.

449
00:34:06,380 --> 00:34:10,250
Dad, is mom leaving us?

450
00:34:45,730 --> 00:34:47,463
You've woken up.

451
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:51,330
I don't know how it started.

452
00:34:51,330 --> 00:34:54,380
I just fell asleep while sitting in the wheelchair.

453
00:34:54,380 --> 00:34:56,880
Maybe the sea breeze was so comfy.

454
00:34:58,530 --> 00:35:00,263
Look here.

455
00:35:00,263 --> 00:35:04,591
Not only is the sand soft, its shell is also quite special.

456
00:35:10,950 --> 00:35:14,200
Mom, look at the shell I've picked up.

457
00:35:28,660 --> 00:35:30,393
Fei Fei.

458
00:35:35,220 --> 00:35:37,390
I knew it's you.

459
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:51,813
Mom.

460
00:35:52,900 --> 00:35:55,200
Why do you like the seaside?

461
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:58,910
I've always liked the sea very much.

462
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:03,870
I like the place where life began.

463
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:07,250
I like everything about the sea.

464
00:36:09,490 --> 00:36:13,810
When I'm in the sanatorium, I think of the sea countless times.

465
00:36:13,810 --> 00:36:15,693
I imagine

466
00:36:16,420 --> 00:36:18,620
I was right here.

467
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:28,660
I heard that people who like the sea are all lovers of freedom.

468
00:36:29,490 --> 00:36:31,770
Sounds plausible.

469
00:36:31,770 --> 00:36:35,490
If you like being here, I'll take you here every day in the coming days.

470
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:51,840
I want to go and sit there.

471
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:54,670
All right, let me wheel you over.

472
00:37:00,290 --> 00:37:02,840
This wheel got stuck in the sand.

473
00:37:07,570 --> 00:37:09,630
Let's walk there.

474
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:17,660
Let me carry you on my back.

475
00:37:17,660 --> 00:37:19,080
Can you do that?

476
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:21,680
I'll try and see if I can. Come on.

477
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,813
Come up here.

478
00:37:29,220 --> 00:37:30,820
We are getting up.

479
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:48,363
Mom.

480
00:37:48,363 --> 00:37:50,690
Can you tell me something about Ji Mingcong?

481
00:37:57,560 --> 00:38:00,360
I had very tradition-minded parents.

482
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:03,060
They couldn't quite understand me.

483
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:07,571
In their eyes, I'd always been a somewhat abnormal person.

484
00:38:07,571 --> 00:38:12,870
And I also thought I needed treatment and I was abnormal.

485
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:18,280
It wasn't until Ji Mingcong's appearance

486
00:38:20,330 --> 00:38:25,000
that I came to realize some people could be eccentric.

487
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,330
Hello.

488
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:28,220
I am Ji Mingcong.

489
00:38:29,870 --> 00:38:33,210
Just like some people enjoy the smell of gasoline,

490
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:36,180
some people like lining up candies in a row

491
00:38:36,180 --> 00:38:39,400
and eat them one by one by color,

492
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:44,290
and some people can understand the sound of seabirds.

493
00:38:45,470 --> 00:38:49,390
What is real and what is fake.

494
00:38:50,380 --> 00:38:54,000
What you can't feel doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

495
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:58,140
And what you can feel doesn't mean it exists.

496
00:38:58,140 --> 00:38:59,913
It's for you.

497
00:39:01,290 --> 00:39:02,360
Thanks.

498
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:07,350
"There is no better gift in the Jiangnan region, I send a plum blossom as a herald of spring."

499
00:39:07,350 --> 00:39:08,913
Some people

500
00:39:08,913 --> 00:39:12,110
always talk about conforming to this world

501
00:39:12,110 --> 00:39:14,390
and changing oneself.

502
00:39:15,490 --> 00:39:18,920
But what is the standard for judging

503
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:21,320
whether someone is normal or not?

504
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:26,010
Have you ever loved Ji Mingcong?

505
00:39:29,420 --> 00:39:33,520
It was because of love that I left.

506
00:39:36,010 --> 00:39:38,010
What about Ye Jicheng?

507
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:42,560
I'm indebted to him after all.

508
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:48,690
Part of his devilish madness comes down to his obsessiveness about me.

509
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:52,500
That's why he is so keen to find me.

510
00:39:53,660 --> 00:39:55,860
How did you know he's looking for you?

511
00:39:57,570 --> 00:40:01,620
Because my eyes are watching all the time.

